{"lc": 1, "type": "constructor", "id": ["langchain", "schema", "document", "Document"], "kwargs": {"metadata": {"producer": "Adobe PDF Library 15.0", "creator": "Adobe InDesign CC 13.1 (Macintosh)", "creationdate": "2018-05-10T14:11:31-04:00", "moddate": "2018-05-10T14:11:34-04:00", "trapped": "/False", "source": "corpus\\Family-Guide-to-Autism1.pdf", "total_pages": 17, "page": 10, "page_label": "8"}, "page_content": "When you are ready to interview respite care  \nproviders, keep in mind that the most important step is \nto observe how the respite worker interacts with your \nchild with autism and your family. If possible, have the \nworker spend supervised time with your family  \nmember. Below is a checklist of what you will want to \ndiscuss with a potential respite worker:\n \u2022 Previous work experience with an individual  \n  with autism \n \u2022 Background checks\n \u2022 Training sessions\n \u2022 Behavioral concerns\n \u2022 Safety issues\n \u2022 Availability and flexibility\n \u2022 Work references \nTo find respite care in your area, please look at our \nonline Resource Guide for your state\u2019s information:  \nAutismSpeaks.org/Resource-Guide.", "type": "Document"}}